==English==

===Etymology===
A cloverleaf junction resembles a four-leafed [[clover]]

===Noun===
A road lane allowing traffic to make an offside turn by a three-quarter circle nearside turn.  Also applied to the complete junction.  

===Notes=== 
As a single word, not usually applied to a biological structure.  For the plural form, ''cloverleafs'' appears more widespread than ''cloverleaves''.

===Verb===
Turn by following a cloverleaf.